-cross-circle copy-heading-link-img" role=3D"img" aria-label=3D"Error copyi=
ng link"></span></button></span></h5><p>GGL1 and GGL2 do not really make se=
nse because it is a mixture of information between real estate type and per=
centage of commercial use what is used most likely for FINMA reporting. Fur=
thermore it seems that GGL1 and GGL2 are not accurate anymore because FINMA=
 did change the definition, what is another strong argument against using i=
t. The recommendation is, to use proper real estate types and calculate the=
 GGL1 and GGL2 in the data product based on "MixedUseRealEstate" and the pe=
rcentage of commercial use. Here is the latest definition from FINMA:<span>=
&nbsp;</span><a style=3D"text-decoration: none;" href=3D"https://www.finma.=
ch/de/~/media/finma/dokumente/dokumentencenter/myfinma/2ueberwachung/sst/im=
mobilien_template_de.pdf?sc_lang=3Dde&amp;hash=3D7AA1C1E9F308048BFBAEEEA54F=
